gomodel:SYNGO_576  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Single, autaptic hippocampal Complexin-1 and -2 double knock-out (DKO) neurons exhibit a decrease in evoked release (EPSC amplitude; Fig. 2A, B; Table 1), but not in the readily-relasable pool size (sucrose response; Fig 2D, E; Table 1).\n\nComplexin-1 and -2 can compensate for the loss of the respective other isoform in hippocampal autaptic neurons: Complexin-1 KO mice and Complexin-2 KO mice are viable and exhibit no deficits in evoked release (Fig 2B), whereas Complexin-1/2 DKO mice die a few hours after birth.\n\nComplexin only regulates synaptic vesicle fusion, since the deficit in synaptic transmission can be rescued by elevating the extracellular calcium concentration (Fig. 5). Experimental description: CPX I and CPX II mutant mice were generated..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_576" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

